# README Screenshots

- Keep a dedicated `## App Screenshots` section at the end of `README.md`.
- Include only high-value screens that provide a quick product overview (avoid clutter).
- Use stable image paths under `public/screenshots/` with clear filenames.
- When a meaningful UI change affects existing screenshots, refresh the impacted images before finalizing.
- If a new major surface is introduced, add at most one additional screenshot and keep the section concise.
